  "doc_id": "41128",
  "text": "Ptr is the causal agent of tan spot of wheat. The pathogen is known to produce two well characterized proteinaceous HSTs, namely PtrToxA and PtrToxB, which interact in a highly specific manner with the host plant and are important determinants of pathogenicity on wheat [CITATION_1] . PtrToxA and PtrToxB induce necrotic and chlorotic symptoms, respectively, on leaves of susceptible wheat genotypes. Sensitivity to one of these toxins renders the host susceptible to the pathogen, while transfer of each individual toxin into a nonpathogenic isolate of the fungus can restore pathogenicity.",
